94. String Types

-- In the string category, there are a bunch of data types.

-- 1. Char(x) :- Use this for storing fixed length strings like abbreviations of states.

-- 2. Varchar(x):- Use this for storing variable length strings like addresses or zipcodes. They can range upto 64Kb.

-- Use varchar(50):- for username and passwords and use varchar(255) for storing addresses.

-- 3. MEDIUMTEXT:- 16 MB.

-- 4. LONGTEXT :- 4GB.


-- Try to choose varchar data type bacause it can be indexed.
